==English==
===Interjection phrase===
'''but hey!'''

#Used to show that what has just been referred to is not [[ideal]] and that the speaker or writer believes it cannot be [[help]]ed or [[improve]]d upon, or is [[unwilling]] to do so.

====Quotations====
*'''2003''': Streaming a movie prevents any but the most dedicated and well-equipped hacker from making a digital copy (pointing a camera at the screen still works, but hey) &mdash; S. Gulie, ''Quicktime for the Web'', Morgan Kaufmann, p136
*'''2004''': I am pretty sure it's another computer glitch, but hey, it's not my fault and it's perfectly legal. &mdash; R. Broadhead, ''Dear Valued Customer, You Are A Loser'', Andrews McMeel Publishing, p89

====Usage notes====
*'''But hey''' is typically followed by a [[justification]], [[explanation]] or [[excuse]] for the circumstances referred to.  It is also used with nothing following it, in which case it stands for "but nothing can be done about this and so it must be accepted".